📄 Written Project Report
🧠 Project Title:
Clinical Pathway Recommendation System (MVP)

🧭 Objective:
The goal of this project is to build a minimal viable product (MVP) of an AI-powered clinical decision support tool that recommends the next best clinical action (e.g., lab test, imaging, treatment) for a patient admitted to a hospital.

It does this by:

Taking the patient’s current clinical condition as input,

Using a trained machine learning model to predict the optimal next step,

Dynamically updating predictions as new actions are taken.

🏗️ Technologies:
Python (data processing and ML)

scikit-learn (modeling and evaluation)

Google Colab (cloud-based execution)

Cursor / VS Code (development)

Git & GitHub (version control)

🗃️ Dataset:
The project uses synthetic data, simulating 1000 hospital admissions with attributes:

Demographics: age, sex

Vitals: blood pressure, heart rate

Chronic conditions: diabetes, heart disease

Symptoms: fever, cough

Target: one of 5 possible clinical actions (e.g., CBC, Chest X-ray, etc.)

🔍 ML Model:
Model used: Random Forest Classifier

Features: Standardized and label-encoded patient attributes

Target: Next clinical action

📊 Evaluation:
Model performs reasonably well in distinguishing among recommended actions.

Classification metrics and confusion matrix offer insight into misclassifications.

Real-time prediction for new synthetic patients is functional.

🚀 Status:
✅ Phase 1: Initial scaffold and GitHub repo set up
✅ Phase 2: Synthetic data generation, ML pipeline, model evaluation, and basic dynamic inference